        title: "Bringing it all together",
        text: "Happiness and peace start with balance in the mind. Many people look for both in the outside world. They drown worries in alcohol, lose themselves in relationships, or try to fill the empty space with someone else's approval. None of that works for long, since trying to avoid negativity only makes the mind focus on it more. You end up thinking about problems without ever solving them. Therapy teaches you to handle stress by finding its roots.\n\nSelf therapy draws on tools from different branches of psychology. It can sound unrealistic, since ten minutes a day does not sound like much. Fortunately, it can change your life. The technique shines a light on the inner part of you, so you can care for, support, and love yourself the way you deserve.\n\nFor many people, therapy looks like paying someone to pick your brain. It just is not so. It is a tool to enrich your life with the positivity, resilience, and peace you already carry inside. It takes effort and a little discomfort, but it is always worth it.\n\nTry this\n\nMake the ten minute self therapy a habit with these tips. Set your alarm earlier and start your day with self analysis and positive thoughts. Keep a separate journal for your evening conclusions and lessons. Pick the same time every day for your walk and the middle section of self therapy. If you get a strong insight, write it down. Keep a record of your progress. Notice how your mindset and behavior shift over a week or a month. That will keep you motivated."
